Genuinely was surprised to see that there's controversy about the author of "Master and Commander", Patrick O'Brian, being "cold, bullying, isolated, snobbish and super-sensitive" and many fans of his books being disheartened. The man who wrote those books COULD NOT be otherwise.
It's like being scandalized by the private life of H. G. Wells. Not only is there no contrast, the creator and creation fits into a perfect organic whole.

If you can find anything about this on the internet it will play it off as just a joke, but American Winston Churchill (even though forgotten now) was a massively popular author in his day, he tried to run for Governor of New Hampshire, but something did not work out, he lost.

7D chess answer: US President Winston Churchill, the American novelist. Him and the British Churchill were friends and British Churchill suggested that American Churchill become President while he becomes Prime Minister so two Winston Churchills rule over Anglo-Saxon civilization

When they became friends American Churchill was actually the more famous of the two, British Churchill actually became PM, but American Churchill never got to be President. But it was a very possible future and would have likely prevented WW2. Potential best Anglo-Saxon timeline.
